  <Docs>
    <summary>Provides the class for HTML server controls that map to HTML DIV elements and can be styled individually for any page.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>When added to a page layout, the CSS classes for this web control can be overridden by using an alternate CSS on a per-page level.</para>
      <para>The <see cref="T:Microsoft.SharePoint.Publishing.WebControls.LayoutDivContainer" /> class inherits <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlContainerControl" />.</para>
      <para>The <see cref="M:System.Web.UI.HtmlControls.HtmlContainerControl.RenderAttributes" /> method is overridden so that for each defined CSS class a new CSS class is added with an extended name, "[original name]-[page title]". </para>
      <para>For example, if the following control is added to the page layout:</para>
      <para>&lt;LayoutDivContainer runat="server" class="fullPageLayout" /&gt;</para>
      <para>it is rendered on the "Home" page as follows:</para>
      <para>&lt;div class="fullPageLayout fullPageLayout-Home" /&gt;</para>
      <para>You then can override the fullPageLayout-Home in the DIV class by using an alternate CSS file.</para>
      <para />
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
